Change: Prevent excluding files explicitly passed to `backup` command

When running `restic backup --exclude-if-present .git /home/user/data`
and `/home/user/.git` exists, restic excluded the `data` directory from
the snapshot. The same patterns also holds for `--exclude-caches`.
Similarly, `restic backup --exclude-larger-than 1M large-file.bin` resulted
in an empty snapshot if the file is larger than one megabyte.

The `backup` command now explicitly tracks which files and directories
were specified and ignores excludes for those. The content of a directory
can still be excluded just as before.

https://github.com/restic/restic/issues/5767
https://github.com/restic/restic/pull/21797
